<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 01 at 5:10PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Davidson County through 545 PM EDT...
At 510 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Linwood, or 8 miles west of Lexington, moving
northwest at 5 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Lexington.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Heavy rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
